name: Human Insulin Peptide Hormone diamond
description:
Insulin is a hormone peptide released from the pancreas and regulates uptake and metabolism of glucose in human cells. Diabetes mellitus (DM) occurs when the body does not produce enough insulin (Type 1) or respond normally to insulin (Type 2), causing glucose levels to be elevated.
